    <!-- COMPONENT 1: DOCUMENTATION INDEXER -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="component-1" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Component 1: Documentation Indexer Service</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Purpose</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                The Documentation Indexer scans the <code>/Comserv/root/Documentation/</code> directory for Template Toolkit (.tt) files, extracts metadata and content, and populates the <code>DocumentationMetadataIndex</code> database table with FULLTEXT search capability.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Responsibilities</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Recursively scan Documentation directory for .tt files</li>
                <li>Parse META blocks from .tt files (title, description, roles, category)</li>
                <li>Extract searchable content from HTML/Template markup</li>
                <li>Determine documentation accessibility based on file-level roles</li>
                <li>Write metadata and content to DocumentationMetadataIndex table</li>
                <li>Generate SHA256 hash for change detection</li>
                <li>Run on application startup and periodically (hourly/daily)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Database Table Used</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>DocumentationMetadataIndex</strong> - Stores indexed documentation with FULLTEXT search (11 columns)
            </p>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Columns</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><code>file_path</code> - Relative path from /Documentation/ (UNIQUE)</li>
                <li><code>title</code> - From META block</li>
                <li><code>searchable_text</code> - FULLTEXT indexed content (no markup)</li>
                <li><code>role_access</code> - JSON array of roles that can view ['admin', 'developer', 'user']</li>
                <li><code>content_hash</code> - SHA256 hash for change detection</li>
                <li><code>indexed_at</code> - Timestamp of index operation</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COMPONENT 2: OLLAMA INTEGRATION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="component-2" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Component 2: Ollama LLM Integration</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Purpose</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                Ollama provides free, open-source language models running locally. This integration allows all users to chat with AI without cloud dependencies or API costs.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Features</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Local Execution:</strong> Models run on same server or network (privacy-focused)</li>
                <li><strong>No API Keys Required:</strong> Open-source models available out of the box</li>
                <li><strong>Model Selection:</strong> Support multiple models (mistral, llama2, neural-chat, etc.)</li>
                <li><strong>Stream Response:</strong> Real-time token streaming for better UX</li>
                <li><strong>Context Window:</strong> Support conversation history in prompts</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Implementation Location</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/LLMOllama.pm</code>
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Methods</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><code>new()</code> - Initialize Ollama client with server URL and model name</li>
                <li><code>is_available()</code> - Health check - verify Ollama server is running</li>
                <li><code>generate_response()</code> - Send prompt and get complete response</li>
                <li><code>stream_response()</code> - Streaming response with tokens in real-time</li>
                <li><code>set_temperature()</code> - Control randomness (0.0 = deterministic, 1.0 = creative)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COMPONENT 3: XAI INTEGRATION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="component-3" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Component 3: XAI (xAI Grok) Integration</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Purpose</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                XAI provides access to advanced cloud-based language models (Grok) via API. Available to developers and admins for superior reasoning and code understanding.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Features</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Advanced Models:</strong> Access to Grok and state-of-the-art models</li>
                <li><strong>Code Understanding:</strong> Superior at analyzing and explaining code patterns</li>
                <li><strong>Real-time Knowledge:</strong> Models trained on recent data</li>
                <li><strong>Developer-Only Access:</strong> Restricted to admin/developer roles</li>
                <li><strong>API-Based:</strong> Cloud integration with rate limiting and usage tracking</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Implementation Location</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/LLMXAI.pm</code>
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Security Considerations</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>API Key Encryption: Store encrypted in AiModelConfig table</li>
                <li>Role-Based Access: Only accessible via developer/admin roles</li>
                <li>Rate Limiting: Per-user limits to control costs</li>
                <li>Audit Logging: Track all API calls with user and purpose</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COMPONENT 4: CHAT CONTROLLER -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="component-4" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Component 4: Chat Controller</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Purpose</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                The Chat Controller is a Catalyst controller that handles HTTP requests for chat interactions. It orchestrates documentation search, LLM selection, response generation, and result storage.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Responsibilities</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Parse incoming chat messages and metadata</li>
                <li>Choose Ollama or XAI based on user role and availability</li>
                <li>Query DocumentationMetadataIndex with user message</li>
                <li>Construct system prompt with search results and context</li>
                <li>Call selected LLM with prompt</li>
                <li>Track and return document citations used</li>
                <li>Store messages and metadata to AiMessage/AiConversation tables</li>
                <li>Graceful fallback if LLM unavailable</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Implementation Location</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Chat.pm</code> (or <code>Chat/AI.pm</code> for AI-specific endpoints)
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Primary Endpoints</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><code>POST /chat/ai/send</code> - Main chat endpoint - accepts message, returns response with citations</li>
                <li><code>GET /chat/ai/conversation/:id</code> - Retrieve conversation history</li>
                <li><code>GET /chat/ai/conversations</code> - List user's conversations</li>
                <li><code>POST /chat/ai/stream</code> - Streaming response endpoint (Server-Sent Events)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COMPONENT 5: ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="component-5" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Component 5: Role-Based Access Control</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Purpose</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                Implement fine-grained role-based access control (RBAC) to ensure users only see documentation and features appropriate for their role.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Access Control by Role</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>guest:</strong> Public documentation sections + Ollama basic models</li>
                <li><strong>user:</strong> User + public documentation + Ollama basic models</li>
                <li><strong>developer:</strong> Dev docs + code search + user docs + Ollama + XAI advanced</li>
                <li><strong>admin:</strong> All documentation + admin features + Ollama + XAI + custom models</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Implementation Location</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/RoleBasedAccessControl.pm</code>
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Database Tables Used</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>DocumentationRoleAccess:</strong> Role-to-documentation-section mappings</li>
                <li><strong>AiModelConfig:</strong> Which models available to which roles</li>
                <li><strong>User:</strong> User role assignments</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Caching Strategy</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                Access control results are cached with 15-minute TTL. Cache invalidates when user roles change or docs updated. Cache key: <code>user_id:role:resource_type:resource_id</code>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SUCCESS CRITERIA -->
    <div class="row" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="success-criteria" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Success Criteria</h2>

